I look forward to going to the Sugar Bowl when I'm in Scottsdale.
Old time ice cream parlors are a vanishing breed in the US.
There are so few places left where you can get an ice cream soda.
That's why I really like this place!
There are so many ice cream treats that are not found elsewhere.
Plus, as others have pointed out, it's nice to see a place that has withstood the test of time---especially in a high growth area.
So many places come and go but the Sugar Bowl remains.
Do pay it a visit if you like ice cream!
The service is friendly and prompt.
Just remember---when you are ready to pay, you don't pay the server, you go to the cash register and pay.

