Stopping in last weekend, their power was out, but since it wasn't too warm outside, we stayed anyway.
And guess what?
The lack of an air conditioner running in the background and no fluorescent lighting was kind of appropriate for this little old school ice cream parlor.
It reminded me of a time when ice cream was just ice cream.
No vegetables or pork products involved.
No liqueurs (unless your dad was drinking a beer while you ate your sundae).
No over analyzing the texture, sweetness, creaminess.
Just ice cream.
Of course there's not a scoop for a dime to be found either, but a scoop for $1.95 is on the menu.
