Sugar Bowl is more of an institution than anything else.
I mean, really, they serve Dreyers Ice Cream.
Having said that, they've definitely got the traditional ice cream/soda fountain vibe going.
Their sandwiches are not bad, they make a decent Reuben and a passable burger.
I've also enjoyed the patty melt.
I think what's really going for Sugar Bowl is that it's a great place for the kids - they love it.
When my daughters were younger, they attended Dance Theatre West, which would hold the final recitals at the Scottsdale Center for Performing Arts.
It became a tradition for everybody to race over to Sugar Bowl after the performance, you had to race, just to find a decent parking spot, and then fill up the Sugar Bowl with little girls in tights and tu-tus.
The staff seemed to take it all in stride and the kids loved it.
The food is ok, the ice cream is nothing special - although they do make a special drink called the "Golden Nugget", which is Orange Sherbet and Vanilla ice cream blended with Sprite for a tasty, cool treat.
I give them four stars because they are a valley institution and they deliver a consistent product every time I've been there.
Nothing fancy, just good, satisfying ice cream treats.

